============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Utilitarianism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   The right action maximizes total happiness for greatest number
Philosopher:  Bentham/Mill
Example:      Sacrifice one to save five if it maximizes total utility

Concept:      Plato's Theory of Forms
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   Physical objects are imperfect copies of eternal abstract Forms
Philosopher:  Plato
Example:      The perfect circle exists only as a Form; drawn circles approximate it

Concept:      Social Contract
Branch:       Political
Definition:   Legitimate authority derives from agreement among individuals
Philosopher:  Hobbes/Locke/Rousseau
Example:      People surrender freedoms to government for security and rights

============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is relativity?
A1: Einstein's relativity: Special (1905) — time dilates,
     mass increases at high speeds; E=mc². General (1915) —
     gravity is curved spacetime; explains black holes and
     expanding universe.

Q2: What is the water cycle?
A2: Water evaporates from oceans/lakes, rises and condenses
     into clouds, falls as precipitation, and flows back via
     rivers and groundwater. Driven by solar energy.

Q3: What is the speed of light?
A3: The speed of light in a vacuum is 299,792,458 meters
     per second (approximately 300,000 km/s), denoted as c.

Q4: What is a programming language?
A4: A programming language is a formal set of instructions
     for computers. High-level languages (Python, Java) are
     human-readable; low-level (Assembly) are closer to
     machine code.

Q5: What is metabolism?
A5: Metabolism is all chemical reactions in an organism
     that maintain life: catabolism (breaking molecules for
     energy) and anabolism (building complex molecules from
     simple ones).

============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Keynesian Economics
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: Government fiscal policy stabilizes economy in recessions
Formula:    AD = C + I + G + NX
Economist:  John Maynard Keynes
Example:    2009 US stimulus; 2020-2021 COVID relief spending

Concept:    Comparative Advantage
Category:   International Trade
Definition: Countries gain by specializing in what they produce most efficiently
Formula:    Compare opportunity cost ratios
Economist:  David Ricardo
Example:    China makes electronics cheaply; USA makes pharma cheaply; both gain trading

Concept:    Compound Interest
Category:   Finance
Definition: Interest calculated on initial principal and accumulated interest
Formula:    A = P(1 + r/n)^(nt)
Economist:  Various
Example:    Einstein allegedly called it the 8th wonder of the world

